Security Best Practices
Operational Security Guidelines
Identity Management:

Request new identity between different research topics
Never reuse the same circuit for sensitive queries
Clear browser data regularly
Query Sanitization:

Avoid personal information in search terms
Use generic, non-attributable language
Vary search patterns and timing
Data Handling:

Encrypt research results
Use secure deletion for temporary files
Avoid saving sensitive data to persistent storage
Network Security:

Verify DNS settings point to Tor
Disable WebRTC and JavaScript when possible
Monitor for IP leaks regularly
